# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# urbanav-mobile (Buyer) — environment variables
# Copy this file to `.env` and fill in the values. Expo reads any
# variable prefixed with EXPO_PUBLIC_ at build time.
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Google OAuth 2.0 Client IDs (FREE — no paid API required)
#
# Step-by-step:
#   1. Visit https://console.cloud.google.com/apis/credentials
#   2. Create (or pick) a project, then: Configure OAuth consent screen
#      → User type: External → Add test users → Save & Publish.
#   3. Credentials → Create Credentials → OAuth client ID. Create THREE:
#        a) Web application
#              Authorized redirect URI: https://auth.expo.io/@YOUR_EXPO_USERNAME/urbanav-mobile
#              (Also add http://localhost:19006 if you test on web.)
#        b) Android
#              Package name : com.urbanav.mobile   (matches app.json → android.package)
#              SHA-1         : from `eas credentials` output, or from your debug keystore
#        c) iOS
#              Bundle ID    : com.urbanav.mobile   (matches app.json → ios.bundleIdentifier)
#   4. Paste each Client ID below. These MUST be the same IDs you
#      add to server/.env as GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID_*.
#
# Notes:
# - Google OAuth/Sign-In is 100% free; only Google Cloud APIs like Maps cost money.
# - For development in Expo Go, the WEB client id is enough (Expo proxy flow).

EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID_WEB=
EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID_ANDROID=
EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID_IOS=
EXPO_PUBLIC_GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID_EXPO=
